Bill Spriggs was a renowned economist who dedicated his career to addressing economic disparities in America. As Chair of the Economics Department at Howard University and Chief Economist for the AFL-CIO, he fought for an economy that benefits all Americans. Coming from a family with a history of public service, Bill's work in government reflected his commitment to serving the public. He was known for his intelligence, wisdom, and belief in the transformative power of economic policies. The author expresses condolences to Bill's family and friends during this time.